# Security Rules

## Secrets
- Never hardcode API keys, tokens, or credentials
- Use environment variables via `process.env` with validation at startup
- Never log secrets — redact before logging
- `.env` files must be in `.gitignore`

## Authentication
- All API routes must use `protectedProcedure` (tRPC) or auth middleware
- No `localStorage` for auth tokens — use httpOnly cookies
- Enforce RBAC: check `ctx.user.role` before data access
- Rate limit auth endpoints (login, register, password reset)

## Data Handling
- Encrypt PII at rest using AES-256
- Validate all inputs with Zod schemas before processing
- Sanitize HTML content to prevent XSS
- Set `Content-Security-Policy` headers
- Use parameterized queries (Prisma handles this)

## Audit Logging
- Every state-changing operation must create an audit log entry
- Audit logs are append-only — never delete or update
- Include: userId, action, resource, timestamp, ipAddress, changes
- Redact PII in log entries where possible

## AI Integration
- Never expose Anthropic API key to client-side code
- Validate and sanitize all prompts sent to Claude
- Rate limit AI classification endpoints
- Log all AI API calls with request/response metadata (redact PII)
- Set maximum token limits on all Claude API calls
